The project doesn't exist on disk yet, so I'll give you the config based on the default **stdio** transport (most common for MCP servers).

Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

Then in VS Code:
1. Open **Copilot Chat** → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the **wrench icon** (Select Tools) → verify your tools appear
3. If tools don't appear, run `dotnet build` and restart the server

> **If your server uses HTTP** (has a `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore` package reference), use this instead:
> ```json
> {
>   "servers": {
>     "MyMcpServer": {
>       "type": "http",
>       "url": "http://localhost:3001"
>     }
>   }
> }
> ```
